<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 MODEL - HEATER AND AIR CONDITIONER BLOWER WITH THERMOSTAT
        TEMPERATURE CONTROL (SLEEPER)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsection id="s08284" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5304-14" date="04/03/2000">
        <title>HEATER AND AIR CONDITIONER BLOWER WITH THERMOSTAT TEMPERATURE CONTROL (SLEEPER)</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>9800
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>11/01/1998</startdate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <para>The sleeper heater and air conditioner system consists of a blower to provide heat or cooling air from
                the cab heater box to the sleeper. The system also includes, at the bunk, a thermostat temperature
                control to regulate the bunk temperature, and a blower control for setting the blower to off, low,
                medium or high speed.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsection>
